\title{Refactoring Playbook}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Playbook for code modernization, architecture migrations, and large-scale refactoring. Provides guidance on characterization testing, strangler fig pattern, incremental migration, and behavior preservation. Use for migrations, modernization, and dependency upgrades.}

\subtree{
\title{Refactoring & Migration Playbook}
\p{This playbook guides missions involving code modernization, architecture migrations, dependency upgrades, or large-scale refactoring. The core challenge: \strong{change implementation while preserving behavior}.}

\subtree{
\title{Key Principle: Tests Before Changes}
\p{Refactoring without tests is just changing code and hoping. Before modifying any code:}

\ul{
\li{If tests exist: ensure they pass and cover the behavior you're changing}
\li{If tests are missing: add characterization tests that capture current behavior first}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Milestone Strategy: Incremental Safe Transformation}
\p{Structure milestones around safe transformation phases:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{characterization} - Add tests capturing current behavior (if missing)}
\li{\strong{scaffold} - Set up new patterns/infrastructure alongside old (strangler fig)}
\li{\strong{migrate-batch-N} - Migrate components incrementally, tests pass after each batch}
\li{\strong{cutover} - Switch to new implementation, remove old code}
\li{\strong{cleanup} - Remove scaffolding, polish}
}

\p{Each batch is one milestone. Never "big bang" - always small, verifiable steps where tests pass after each commit.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Worker Types}
\p{Refactoring missions use workers that coordinate through shared state in \code{\startverb .factory/library/\stopverb}.}

\subtree{
\title{characterization-worker}
\p{Adds tests for existing behavior before any changes.}

\ol{
\li{Read \code{\startverb migration-plan.md\stopverb} to understand what's being migrated}
\li{Identify code paths that lack test coverage}
\li{Write characterization tests that capture current behavior (not ideal behavior)}
\li{Update \code{\startverb migration-status.md\stopverb} with test coverage status}
}

\p{Tests must pass against current code. These tests become the safety net for migration.}
}

\subtree{
\title{scaffold-worker}
\p{Sets up new infrastructure to coexist with old (strangler fig pattern).}

\ol{
\li{Read \code{\startverb migration-plan.md\stopverb} for target architecture/patterns}
\li{Create new modules/infrastructure alongside existing code}
\li{Set up adapters/facades so old code can gradually switch to new}
\li{Update \code{\startverb migration-status.md\stopverb} with scaffold status}
}

\p{Old tests must still pass. New infrastructure should be testable but not yet used.}
}

\subtree{
\title{migration-worker}
\p{Migrates specific components from old to new implementation.}

\ol{
\li{Read \code{\startverb migration-status.md\stopverb} to find next component to migrate}
\li{Migrate ONE component/module (keep scope small)}
\li{Update call sites to use new implementation}
\li{Run full test suite - must pass before completing}
\li{Update \code{\startverb migration-status.md\stopverb} marking component as migrated}
}

\p{Each migration is one atomic commit. If tests fail, fix or revert - never leave broken.}
}

\subtree{
\title{verification-worker}
\p{Ensures behavior is preserved across the migration.}

\ol{
\li{Read \code{\startverb migration-status.md\stopverb} to understand what changed}
\li{Run full test suite including characterization tests}
\li{Perform manual verification of migrated functionality}
\li{Compare old vs new behavior for edge cases}
\li{Document any behavioral differences found}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Information Flow}
\pre{\startverb
characterization-worker ──writes──▶ migration-status.md (test coverage)
                                            │
                                            ▼ reads
scaffold-worker ──writes──▶ migration-status.md (scaffold ready)
                                            │
                                            ▼ reads
migration-worker ──writes──▶ migration-status.md (component X migrated)
                                            │
                                            ▼ reads
verification-worker ──writes──▶ migration-status.md (batch verified)
\stopverb}

\p{Each worker:}

\ol{
\li{Reads migration-plan.md and migration-status.md before starting}
\li{Ensures all tests pass before marking work complete}
\li{Updates migration-status.md after completing}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Orchestrator Setup}
\p{Before starting migration, create:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{\code{\startverb .factory/library/migration-plan.md\stopverb}}:}
\li{Current state (what exists now)}
\li{Target state (what we're migrating to)}
\li{Scope (what's included, what's explicitly excluded)}
\li{Approach (strangler fig, parallel run, etc.)}
\li{Risk areas (complex logic, external dependencies)}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{\code{\startverb .factory/library/migration-status.md\stopverb}}:}
\li{Components list with status (pending, in-progress, migrated, verified)}
\li{Test coverage status}
\li{Scaffold status}
\li{Issues/blockers discovered}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{\code{\startverb .factory/services.yaml\stopverb}} - Ensure \code{\startverb test\stopverb} command runs full suite}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Feature Structure}
\subtree{
\title{Characterization Phase}
\pre{\startverb
characterize-<area>  (characterization-worker) - Add tests for <area>
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Scaffold Phase}
\pre{\startverb
scaffold-<component> (scaffold-worker) - Set up new <component> alongside old
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Migration Batches}
\pre{\startverb
migrate-<component>  (migration-worker) - Migrate <component> to new implementation
verify-batch-N       (verification-worker) - Verify batch N preserves behavior
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Cutover & Cleanup}
\pre{\startverb
cutover-<area>       (migration-worker) - Remove old <area>, switch fully to new
cleanup-<area>       (migration-worker) - Remove adapters, polish
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example Worker Skill: migration-worker}
\pre{\startverb
---
name: migration-worker
description: Migrate components from old to new implementation incrementally.
---

# Migration Worker

## Procedure

1. **Read status** - Check `migration-plan.md` and `migration-status.md`. Identify your assigned component. Return to orchestrator if scaffold not ready.

2. **Understand the component** - Read current implementation. Identify all call sites. Note edge cases and error handling.

3. **Migrate incrementally**:
   - Update component to use new patterns/infrastructure
   - Update call sites one at a time
   - Run tests after each change
   - Keep changes in atomic commits

4. **Verify** - Run full test suite. All tests must pass.

5. **Update status** in `migration-status.md`:
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{UserService}
\p{\strong{Status:} MIGRATED \strong{Commit:} abc123 \strong{Changes:} Migrated from class to functional, now uses new data layer \strong{Call sites updated:} 12 \strong{Tests:} All 47 tests pass}

\pre{\startverb

## Example Handoff

\stopverb}

\p{{ "salientSummary": "Migrated UserService to the functional pattern and updated 12 call sites; ran \code{\startverb npm test\stopverb} (47 passing) and updated \code{\startverb .factory/library/migration-status.md\stopverb} with the MIGRATED status + commit.", "whatWasImplemented": "Migrated UserService from class-based to functional pattern. Updated 12 call sites. All 47 existing tests pass.", "verification": { "commandsRun": [ {"command": "npm test", "exitCode": 0, "observation": "47 tests pass"}, {"command": "grep 'Status: MIGRATED' .factory/library/migration-status.md", "exitCode": 0, "observation": "Status updated"} ] } }}

\pre{\startverb

## Return to Orchestrator When

- Scaffold not ready for this component
- Tests fail and fix is non-trivial
- Migration reveals architectural issue requiring plan change
- Component has undocumented dependencies
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Pitfalls}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Changing behavior during migration} - Refactoring changes structure, not behavior. Behavior changes are separate features.}
\li{\strong{Big bang migrations} - Each commit should leave tests passing. Never batch multiple components.}
\li{\strong{Skipping characterization} - Without tests capturing current behavior, you can't verify preservation.}
\li{\strong{Incomplete call site updates} - Use grep/find-references to ensure all usages are updated.}
\li{\strong{Not updating migration status} - Next worker needs to know what's done.}
\li{\strong{Mixing refactoring with features} - Keep them separate. Refactor first, then add features.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Stop}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Complete} - All components migrated, verified, old code removed}
\li{\strong{Blocked} - Discovered issue requiring architectural decision}
\li{\strong{Scope change} - User decides to adjust what's being migrated}
}
}
}